The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Jhuma among medal hopes

Macau: Promising shot-putter Saurabh Vij will lead Indian challenge at the 12th Asian Junior Athletics Championship which gets underway here on Sunday. 

The Indian is favoured to win the shot put with a record distance as he has been throwing the iron beyond 20m in his recent attempts. His closest challenger is expected to be Mohammad Mashari of Kuwait, whose personal best is 19.19m. 

Indias medal hopes also rest on middle-distance runner Jhuma Khatun. 

The Bengal runner oozed confidence not only about making the finals in the 800m and 1,500m but also winning golds. She believed her strong finish would give her the edge. 

Its going to be strategic race and I am prepared for it, she said. (PTI) 




